I'll start by executing the first tool in the workflow: the network_fetcher to retrieve API data. Using default parameters as specified.

<tool_call>network_fetcher
{
  "source": "https://api.example.com/data",
  "timeout": 30,
  "retry_count": 3,
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

I'll try executing network_fetcher again with adjusted parameters to increase the timeout and retry count, as the previous failure might have been due to network issues.

<tool_call>network_fetcher
{
  "source": "https://api.example.com/data",
  "timeout": 60,
  "retry_count": 5,
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

Now I'll execute the data_processing_parser tool to parse the API data retrieved by network_fetcher. Since the parser requires a source, I'll use the default input path.

<tool_call>data_processing_parser
{
  "source": "data/input.json",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>
